ok so since the order has been confirmed, here's my personal storyline theory.
In heading home, 23800 becomes part of the ancient walkers, and she warns them of the meteors, and they all go down the well which has some technology to keep them safe all into the future, where 23800 starts to remember what happened back then. In ON my Way, she starts to research what happened, and she finds the monolith. In alone p2, she gets famous for this, but thinks there still something there, so she goes to Vietnam and finds what was there. After that, she goes back and puts out a call fro all the walkers, spreading the word. Then in sing me to sleep, she and 0 and one more walker, are lost in the city and they find the first drone. In Tired, I think it's what zero remembered of the walkers who didn't survive the meteor, and faded is where he's trying to find the walkers whos survived it. And then in all falls down, after the call is put out, some teenagers who will become the new generation of walkers find the time capsules left by the original walkers and inside the drones and the descendants of the surviving walkers, the walkers with the white robes, find the new walkers. Then in darkside, the old and the new meet and begin to work together, with them finding and scanning the old walker city from heading home in diamond heart. 

There's a couple plot holes, but it's my personal theory.

comment_text: Once there lived a girl named *LILY* in a castle with her rich and royal family. She was not allowed to go out to play and no one wanted to be her friend. She started talking with animals and always used to look at stars and count them. Her step mother did not love her. She didn't get the love of a mother from an early age. She always felt *LONELY* she was *FADED* . She always thought that she does not even have a *DIAMOND HEART* but still everyone hates her. She  *LOST CONTROL* and ran away from there. The whole kingdom started finding her but they can't find. She started living in a small town. One day she met a boy named Trev on a rainy day wearing black cloak Lily was wet in the rain the boy asked her to come under her umberella. They started talking about each other on their way home. She told the boy that no one likes her and she is lonely. The boy asked her to come with him in his magic world. He gave her headphones. She wore it and they both held each other's hand. They were in the *DIFFERENT WORLD* where everything was opposite from Earth. It was a fantasy world. The boy was a sorcerer he made a beautiful world with his superior magic where no one can come. Their stories were same, they fell in love. They did many adventures. The girl wanted to go back on Earth for some time to meet her father. The boy let her go she promised him that she will come back here soon. She got to know that her father loves her very much. She stayed with him till his death. After her father's funeral she again started feeling lonely. She wore the headphones and came back to the boy's world. But nothing was same the colourful world was destroyed. Everything went dark and black. A boy was standing there in black hoodie and mask his name was Alan. He told the girl that the boy was a bad sorcerer, he lost his parents and after his sacrifices he became superior. But he did crimes so he was punished by a good witch. He can't control his body. The witch said that he will be only freed when someone like you starts loving you. His powers will be taken away from him and he will rebron on Earth to proof that he's good. He had ignited when she has gone and he took rebirth after few months in a good family. Now he has to proof himself. Lily said, "Again I lost my loved one. Why always me? So many sacrifices...." Alan gave her a mask and asked her to come with him in the Walker World. She met many good people. She enjoyed the adventures. But after 20 years she is still waiting for that boy when she is 36. Maybe they will meet again and that love story will continue. Ofcourse they will meet.\n\nSorry for my bad english. And I didn't think much about the story when I was writing it. So it's just something stupid. I hope that Alan will read this. Btw I wanted to watch a movie inspired by Alan Walker. But it's only a dream and it will never come true.

comment_text:
Alright I hope this gets noticed by someone at least here we go! raw notes time! Then I'll do a little conclusion/tl:dr. Ok so I saw a theory on "Heading home" and decided to give it a shot. 

Heading Home: A person researching about ancient civilizations which had futuristic technology and knew of a mass extinction event coming soon, eventually they bury their time capsules and seal them away for people of the future (If any in their mind) to find. 

On My Way : The person finds one of the time capsules/signs and now has proven said civilization is real. 

Alone Pt.II: the person, now appears to be trying to find a temple like the one in the first song in chronological order I think. 

Alone: Ok, This episode, oohhhh boy I don't understand one second of it. "Walker" The main guy with the pink name is the leader, presumably Alan Walker, calls the walkers to a place in the world on a mountain side. (also worth being noted the words being said in the chat might mean something?) Then all the Walkers join on the cliff side and over look a city and take off their mask. Thats all I have here. It's got to be related to the old civilization some how though.

Sing Me To Sleep: Even more puzzled on this one than on alone... Is it all a simulation? I have no idea, lets keep going to get more context though.

Tired: uh... A meteor comes in to strike the world or something like a solar flare, but more lethal turning off all of the power, although the walkers make some kind of device that has a blue light and a lightbulb on top, so that's cool I guess. 

Faded: A man tries to find his home after the apocalypse strikes, obviously somewhere between 5-10 years. When he finds his home, he only finds the concrete frame of what used to be, maybe that was blown away in the incident, and whatever, or whoever was inside of it was vaporized as well? Maybe people raided it of all of its materials and left it only stripped down to the concrete frame?

All Falls Down: after the apocalyptic incident, not many people survived, however some have holed up inside of an old hotel/apartment building. They begin to dig up the Lost Ancient Civilization's time capsule, in which were the walker's uniform, (I guess), and the walker signs, in which it calls the walkers to meet possibly? 

Darkside: some (old walkers? asian dudes who know how to use these? African dudes maybe?) teach the people who found the walker logos how to use them, they appear to be drones, they learn how to use these to scan things, and so some how they find a building they need to scan, and so they scan it and then the drones fly away.

Diamond Heart: the end of the line, the board predicted that a city would be built, and they finally built it years and years after the incident. Soooo lemme copy and paste everything into one comment on heading home.


Chronological Timeline so far imo: A woman researches and figures out that there might be truth behind this Futuristic Ancient Civilization, so she goes and finds it and gets it excavated and finds out it is true. They then try to find the temple board because why not. I don't know? The walkers gang is formed here, and they meet up, that's all I know. Glitchy world, but now the walkers are called to China/Japan. World apocalypse/meteor/solar flare! Yay. Some man's sob story as he tries to find his house and the dead people and stuff. Later on, probably like at least 20 years later some people dig up the old civilization's time capsules. Then they learn that the WVs are drones! and then the drones scan a city into existence.

Tl:dr Woman finds futuristic civilization, gang is made inspired by it's tech and logo, then the world ends and they build a walker utopia.

comment_text:
A little over four months ago, I've suffered a Ring avulsion injury. Wouldn't wish that on anyone.
While I am still recovering and grateful for the successful surgically reattachment, I feel the need to share that "Heading home" had a huge part in the healing process. In the Hospital, I've listened to it about 20 times a day, finding comfort in the lyrics and melody.
With my wife and daughters supporting me, it brought a different meaning to the ending of the third verse 
"You were high on Love, I was drunk, drunk on the pain" 

For me, Heading Home might be your finest work.

Thank you Alan Walker.

comment_text:
*clears throat*

Okay, so I saw someone else compose a massive theory, about WoW, and I've decided to try my take on it.

Alan has said that the chronological order is Heading Home, On My Way, Alone Pt 2, Alone, Sing me to sleep, Tired, Faded, All Falls Down, Darkside, Diamond Heart.

My guess is that Heading Home is in the past, where the Walkers live in a sort of utopia. One Walker spots an incoming (or rather, several incoming) meteors, heading straight for them. She warns another Walker, and all the Walkers get into a bunker, and presumably live, but lose their memory or something. 
Fast forward to the modern world, the same Walker who warned them sees some paintings and stuff at a museum, and it sparks some memories. She decides to research more on it, and discovers the stones in On My Way. This leads to the discovery of the artifacts from Heading Home.
Alone Part two shows the discovery of even more Walker technology, which leads to Alone, where presumably more Walkers start remembering, and all gather together at an unknown place.
Sing me to sleep is featuring even more of this, showing Walkers roaming the streets, and communicating through messages.
Tired features the fact a solar flare will hit the land, and the Walkers once again, bunker down to survive. They watch as the timer hits Zero, and the flare hits.
Faded shows the ruins of the flare, and one Walker travelling them, motivated by an old, torn picture of a house. They travel everywhere, and find it, only to be torn by the fact that it is ruined just like everything else.
All Falls Down shows a group of survivors, who find the Walkers old technology, but do not know how to use it. A group of surviving Walkers help them out in the night, and show them how to do so.
Darkside shows the two groups of Walkers, old and new, teaming together to scan places and recreate the utopia in Heading Home.
Diamond Heart shows them burying some of the technology, presumably for future generations, seeing as so many things happen at the peak of their utopia. 

I havent watched some of the videos in a while, so this might be inaccurate, but I hope that this was okay, and yes, I am aware someone else did something like this, this was just my take on it.
